\section{Principle Component and Least Squares}
\begin{enumerate}
	\item  Use the function \verb|np.random.multivariate_normal()| to create samples $(x_i,y_i) \in \mathbb{R}^2$ for $i = 1,\dots, 100$ from a 2-dimensional multivariate normal distribution
	with mean $\mu := (0,0)$ and covariance $$\Sigma := \begin{bmatrix}
	1&0.7\\
	0.7&1
	\end{bmatrix}.$$
	\item Solve the least squares problem
		\begin{align*}
			\min \limits_{a} \sum_{i=1}^{100} ( ax_i - y_i )^2
		\end{align*}
		and plot the solution and the data points.
	\item Make a principle component analysis of the data $v_i := (x_i,y_i) \in \mathbb{R}^2$ (note $m=2$ and $n=100$) and plot the first principle component into the plot of (ii).
\end{enumerate}
